snippet.textDisplay: That was the perfect Birthday present for me. I thought we were absolutely brilliant in the first half but looked kinda jaded in the second and set up a nervy finish when we conceded deep into injury time. But that doesn't matter cos we are into the next round. I thought Martinez was a bit shaky. I don't understand why he was cluttering into our CBs time after time. Bellerin was decent. Saka was OUTSTANDING. He scored a banger and was a threat going forward. He really is making me eat my words cos I didn't think he was good enough to play in the first team. What a talent. Mustafi was playing very well up until he got injured. I am gutted for him. Wishing him a speedy recovery. Sokratis was decent. Xhaka did well again. Willock was brilliant. He was by far and away our MOTM. He was involved in both goals and was industrious as well.This was much better from the youngster and hopefully he ends the season strongly. Guendouzi had a really good game. Pepe was dreadful again. He has all these skills and tricks but the end product is still lacking. He has to sort that out. Martinelli was really good. He was involved in the first goal and his work rate was superb again. Eddie was superb. He took his goal really well and put in a real shift. Hopefully he gets more minutes cos we have a talent in there. Ceballos did all right when he came on. Holding was pretty poor. He switched off for their goal and I don't get what people see in this guy. He is not good enough. Arteta got his team selection spot on. Can't fault him. Overall it was a job well done and it was a perfect way to round off my Birthday. Onto the next round. COYG!!!!!
